title: For Sale:  ULTRA RARE! Crye Precison JPC prototype Multicam
postcontent: I have an origional Crye Precision JPC Prototype ( size Large)  These are sometimes referred to as Slick JPCs Due to the fact that the upper MOLLE rows found on commercially available JPC's are not present on these. Besides the upper rows of MOLLE being replaced by Velcro there are other differences between this model and the commercial variant such as:The shoulder straps being laser cut Multicam material instead of the standard Coyote Brown materialThis JPC also lacks the integrated magazine pouches on the front and instead simply has 3 rows of MOLLEInstead of the cummerbund wrapping entirely around the body and attaching via Velcro under a center mounted flap they attach under flaps that are on the included side plate pockets much like a maritime CIRAS.This version of the JPC comes with side plate pockets which the standard version does not includeThese were only made and offered under government contract to JSOC and were never offered commercially. Most publicly available photographs show this particular variant being used by CAG (1st SOFD-D) and the 75th Ranger Regimental Reconnaissance Detachment. The user also has the option to remove the cummerbunds and side plate pockets and instead use one single strap attached to the rear plate bag on each side that buckles into a female buckle sewn on the front plate bag. These Carriers are extremely rare. This one has never been worn and is in new condition.
